    <td>A-</td>
    <td port="p10r">10</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td port="p11l">11</td>
    <td>B+</td>
    <td port="p11r">11</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td port="p12l">12</td>
    <td>B-</td>
    <td port="p12r">12</td>
   </tr>
  </table>
 </td></tr>
 <tr><td>
  <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" cellborder="1"><tr>
   <td balign="left">18-50 VDC. Common-cathode signal: Mega D8/D10/D9 drive PUL+/DIR+/ENBL+; PUL-/DIR-/ENBL- jumpered to Mega GND. DIP SW1-8 = ON OFF OFF OFF ON OFF OFF ON: 128 microstep (25600 pulse/rev), 3.76 A peak / 2.69 A RMS, SW4 OFF = half current. Higher current because it drives TWO motors in parallel (~1.88 A each). EN active-LOW (firmware).</td>
  </tr></table>
 </td></tr>
</table>
