   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td port="p9l">9</td>
    <td>COM+</td>
    <td port="p9r">9</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td port="p10l">10</td>
    <td>LEDout</td>
    <td port="p10r">10</td>
   </tr>
  </table>
 </td></tr>
 <tr><td>
  <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" cellborder="1"><tr>
   <td balign="left">Logic side: active-LOW; IN1 = shelf 1 … IN6 = shelf 6. VCC + coil supply (JD-VCC) both off the Mega's USB-fed 5 V (VCC↔JD-VCC jumper in place). Contact side: in THIS rig a SINGLE relay channel switches ALL the LEDs at once — every shelf's string is paralleled on a terminal block, so all lights go on/off together — even though the board has 6 channels and the firmware drives 6 relay pins (a build-specific simplification). COM+ = fused +24 V into that channel's common; LEDout = its switched output to the LED terminal block.</td>
  </tr></table>
 </td></tr>
</table>
> fillcolor="#FFFFFF" shape=box style=filled]
	FUSE_LED [label=<
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
 <tr><td>
  <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" cellborder="1"><tr>
   <td balign="left">FUSE_LED</td>
  </tr></table>
 </td></tr>
 <tr><td>
  <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" cellborder="1"><tr>
   <td balign="left">Fuse — size to LED load, fast-blow (inline holder)</td>
   <td balign="left">2-pin</td>
  </tr></table>
 </td></tr>
 <tr><td>
  <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" cellborder="1">
   <tr>
    <td port="p1l">1</td>
    <td>in</td>
    <td port="p1r">1</td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td port="p2l">2</td>
    <td>out</td>
    <td port="p2r">2</td>
   </tr>
  </table>
 </td></tr>
 <tr><td>
  <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" cellborder="1"><tr>
   <td balign="left">On the +24 V leg feeding the shelf-LED relay contacts. Amps = total LED watts / 24 V, next standard size up, kept below the relay's contact rating. LED load wattage still TBD (see hardware-open-questions.md).</td>
  </tr></table>
 </td></tr>
</table>
